  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mitigation of further deterioration of vulnerable people&#x2019;s health and nutrition status during flood shocks</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to mitigate a further deterioration of vulnerable women and children&#x2019;s health and nutrition status ahead of and during a projected severe flood shock. This WFP project will identify and treat cases of moderate acute malnutrition through the provision of specialized food, among others. The project provides nutrition assistance to 9,076 people, including 4,556 women, 1,945 boys, 2,575 girls, and 1,361 people with disabilities.</narrative>
  </description>
